--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Conversation Status
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Button                   PC

1234567812               1234567812
STATUS IAB      -->      ACK
OK              <-/


1234567812               1234567812
ACK/NACK        <--      STATUS S B
                \->      OK

1234567812               1234567812
STATUS IAB      <--      STATUS G
                \->      ACK/NACK
OK              <-/

1234567812               1234567812
ALIVE            -->     ACK
OK               <-/

1234567812               1234567812
ACK              <--     ALIVE
                 \->     OK

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Message Frame
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 8 Byte  2 Byte
/------\/\
1234567812
TEXT    AB

TEXT = STATUS I, STATUS S, STATUS G, ALIVE, ACK, NACK          Command
A = 0, 1                                                       Button Status
B = 0, 1, 2                                                    LED Status

STATUS I:
Is send by Button and stands for "Status Is". It sends the current LED and 
Button status.

STATUS S:
Is send by PC and stands for "Status Set". It sets the LED status to specific 
state.

STATUS G:
Is send by PC and stands for "Status Get". It requests the information about the
state of button and LED.

ALIVE:
Can be send by PC and Button. It requests information about the alive status of 
the partner.

A: Button Status
0 Button open
1 Button closed

B: LED Status
0 LED off
1 LED permanently on
2 LED blinking on

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Conversation time
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Each message is send until an expected answer is received or a limit of 5 is 
reached. Between each resend you should wait 2 seconds.
